===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm}} {{term|pilot|lang=frm}}, {{term|pillot}}, from {{etyl|it}} {{term|piloto}}, from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|pillottus}}; perhaps ultimately from {{etyl|el}} {{term|πηδόν|tr=pēdon||blade of an oar, oar}} [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?layout.reflang=greek;layout.refembed=2;layout.refwordcount=1;layout.refdoc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057;layout.reflookup=phdo%2Fn;layout.refcit=entry%3Dphda%2Flion;doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3D%2382908  ], hence also [[Ancient Greek|Ancient]] and [[Modern Greek]] [[πηδάλιον]] (''pēdalion''), "rudder" [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3D%2382894].

